                <h1>Anomaly Research Division (A.R.D)</h1>
            </div>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/home">Back</a>
        </div>
        <p>A.R.D is Enigma Corporation's public exploration program for unstable anomaly sectors. Explorers remotely deploy E-Units, recover sector data, route discoveries into research, and influence future operations through council voting.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>How The A.R.D Loop Connects</h2>
        <h3>1. Detection and Entry</h3>
        <p>When a spatial anomaly appears, A.R.D assigns an E-Unit and opens remote access to certified explorers. Every expedition contributes operational data back to Enigma Corporation.</p>
        <h3>2. Recovery and Sectorization</h3>
        <p>Successful anomaly clears can produce persistent sectors. Each sector keeps its own record: owner, founder, value, artwork, and completion history.</p>
        <h3>3. Research and Governance</h3>
        <p>Recovered sectors flow into two connected systems: the exchange (for trading and reserve movement) and analysis (for daily MN and research depth). Those contributions increase explorer influence in council sessions.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Connected Core Systems</h2>
        <h3>Solo Expeditions</h3>
        <p>Generated and saved sectors use room-specific puzzle locks, timed expeditions, and permanent loss if a live sector is abandoned.</p>
        <h3>Co-op Operations</h3>
        <p>Two explorers can run a synchronized expedition with live invites, shared room progression, ready checks, and coordinated finish conditions.</p>
        <h3>Exchange, Analysis, and Council</h3>
        <p>Sectors can be listed, sold, and analyzed for daily MN. Reserve flow and analysis depth feed directly into the same governance loop used for council voting.</p>
        <h3>Explorer Consoles</h3>
        <p>Console records tie it all together: activity, sector ownership, analysis totals, contact status, and current operational presence.</p>
    </section>

